  "prompt": "What are some ways of fixing a tongue thrust?",
  "response": "Here are some methods to help correct a tongue thrust:\n\n1. Speech Therapy\n- Professional assessment and personalized exercises\n- Techniques to retrain tongue placement\n- Specific muscle strengthening exercises\n\n2. Myofunctional Therapy\n- Exercises to improve tongue muscle control\n- Retraining proper tongue positioning\n- Strengthening oral muscles\n\n3. Orthodontic Appliances\n- Special devices to guide tongue placement\n- Helping retrain muscle memory\n- Professional fitting and guidance\n\n4. Awareness and Practice Techniques\n- Consciously placing tongue behind front teeth\n- Practicing correct swallowing technique\n- Regular mirror practice\n\n5. Exercises\n- Tongue-strengthening exercises\n- Practicing correct tongue placement\n- Facial muscle exercises\n\n6. Posture Correction\n- Maintaining proper head and neck alignment\n- Supporting overall muscle coordination\n\n7. Breathing Exercises\n- Promoting nasal breathing\n- Reducing mouth breathing\n\n8. Behavioral Modifications\n- Identifying and addressing underlying habits\n- Stress management techniques\n\n9. Oral Habit Elimination\n- Stopping thumb-sucking or prolonged pacifier use\n- Breaking related childhood oral habits\n\nProfessional consultation is recommended for personalized treatment.",
